# Lab Four - Reusable Barrier Class

This project shows an implementation of a reusable barrier class that employs a custom Semaphore clas.  
**Author:** Adrien Dudon

## Requirements
- Compatible with **Linux** only
- A C++11 compiler (g++ will do fine)
- The Make program (should be already installed on your distro)

## Install
1. Clone this repository: `git clone git@github.com:Deewens/CDDLabs.git`
2. Go to Lab3/ directory: `cd Lab4`
3. Build project: `make CLEAN && make`
4. Run: `./reusableBarrier`

## Project/files Content
- **Barrier:** the barrier implementation, require Semaphore class
- **Sempahore:** implemetation of a Semaphore
- **main.cpp:** the traditional start point of the program, showing off the Barrier implentation

